<div class="section_title">Sixth  Annual Exhibitor Workshop Draws Record Crowd</div>
<span class="text">

<P><IMG height=130 src="/print/images/ces_photos/2k7CESExhWor1.jpg" width=200 align=right>The sixth annual CES Exhibitor Workshop had a record crowd this year with the debut of a breakfast keynote speaker on October 3 at the Las Vegas Convention Center in Las Vegas, Nev.<BR><BR>More than 60 exhibitors, including 35 first-time exhibitors, were present as Dan Hanover, editor and publisher, Event Marketer and Event Design Magazine, kicked things off with the first keynote address in workshop history, addressing best practices for “Building Your 360 Degree Brand.”<BR><BR>CEA VP Sales and Business Development Dan Cole hosted the workshop, which included presentations by Katie Swearingen and Gaiya Sims on CES operations, Liz Burns from GES, Wendy Hudak on CES promotional opportunities, Allison Carney with a public relations overview and Susan Littleton, VP of marketing, on CES marketing tools.<BR><BR>Exhibitors visited the CES vendor fair,&nbsp;spoke one on one with more than 25 vendors and&nbsp;got the inside scoop on&nbsp;CES SmartBooth, powered by BDMetrics. The day wrapped up with an expert panel Q&amp;A session and tours of both the LVCC and Sands/Venetian exhibit space.<BR><BR>If you missed the workshop or want to experience it again <A href="/print/exhibitors/resource_center/workshop/default.asp">check out the webcast</A>.&nbsp;</P>
</span>
